videoSnippet.title: Praggnanandhaa's Last Move as Non GM
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator 6/23/2018 â€“ In a small town of northern Italy called Ortisei, history is being made. The young uber-prodigy R. Praggnanandhaa is playing the 4th Gredine Open 2018 and he has qualified for his final GM norm making him the second youngest GM in the history of the game.

Read full article here https://en.chessbase.com/post/praggnanandhaa-a-game-away-from-becoming-a-grandmaster

Rameshbabu Praggnanandhaa vs Luca Moroni
Gredine Open Chess, JUN-23 2018 
Ruy Lopez: Cozio Defense (C60)

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nge7 4. c3 g6 5. d4 exd4 6. cxd4 Bg7 7. d5 a6 8. Be2 Ne5 9. Nxe5 Bxe5 10. Nc3 d6 11. O-O c5 12. dxc6 bxc6 13. Bh6 d5 14. Qd3 Be6 15. f4 Qb6+ 16. Kh1 dxe4 17. Nxe4 Rd8 18. Qa3 Bd4 19. Bg5 c5 20. Nf6+ Bxf6 21. Bxf6 Rg8 22. Rad1 Rxd1 23. Rxd1 Nd5 24. Bh4 Kf8 25. Bf3 Qb5 26. Bxd5 Bxd5 27. Qe3 g5 28. Bxg5 Qc6 29. Qe7+ Kg7 30. Qe5+ f6 31. Qxd5 Qxd5 32. Rxd5 fxg5 33. Rxg5+
